AMONGST some Tracts published within the year for the resolution of such doubts, as the Dissenters from our Church plead for refusing Communion with it, there was one that respected the use of Indifferent things in the Worship of God. This some one of our Brethren chose to examine and to begin his debate with;
Case examined, p. 2. in the management of which whether he hath dealt closely and ingenuously to use his own words)p. 16.
I shall take the liberty to enquire, and must leave others to judge.

This I proved from the old Testament and New,
from the practice of the Primitive and Modern Churches,
and from their own Concessions.
